Indian Equities Mover: Adani Power, Camlin, TCS, Tata Motors

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i   a n d   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-07-15T10:56:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/indian-equities-mover-adani-power-camlin-tcs-tata-motors.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.  India ’s Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
slid 0.3 percent to 18,561.92. The BSE200 Index fell 0.3 percent
to 2,307.37.  Adani Power Ltd. (ADANI)   gained 1.6 percent to 113.65
rupees, its highest since more than five weeks. Part of India’s
Adani group of companies chaired by billionaire Gautam Adani had
about 5 million shares traded in a single block on National
Stock Exchange today, according to Bloomberg data. The buyers
and sellers weren’t immediately known.  Camlin Ltd. (CAMLN)   lost 1.4 percent to 73.9 rupees, the
most in a week. The Mumbai-based stationary company’s net income
for the three months ended June fell 34 percent to 62.5 million
rupees, according to an exchange filing.  Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS)   climbed 2 percent
to 1,146.05 rupees, its highest since July 13. India’s largest
software maker provider’s first-quarter profit rose 28 percent
to 23.8 billion rupees after clients outsourced more computer
services, the company said yesterday after markets closed.  Tata Motors Ltd. (TTMT)   sank 3.3 percent to 1,033.05
rupees, the most in almost a month. India’s biggest truckmaker’s
global group sales fell in June to 89,846 vehicles from 90,702
units a year earlier, according to an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
